      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the most important SEO tool for a contractor?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content creation tools. Contractors rank by publishing relevant content: service pages, city pages, blog articles, GBP posts. Tracking tools measure rankings but content drives improvement. theStacc publishes 30 articles monthly at $99/month — the highest-output option at the lowest per-article cost.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many blog articles does a contractor need per month?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Top-ranking contractors publish 15–30 monthly. Minimum maintenance requires 4–8 articles; fewer rarely impacts competitive markets. Most contractors don't publish at all, which is why the bar is lower than you'd expect in many markets.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do contractors need different SEO than other local businesses?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Contractors face distinct multi-service, multi-city complexity. A dentist ranks for dental keywords in one city; contractors manage kitchen remodels, bathrooms, roofing, and additions across 20–50 mile territories. You need content covering every service-city combination.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long does SEO take for contractors?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">First ranking movements appear in 60–90 days. Meaningful lead generation typically starts in 3–6 months. Competitive keywords require 6–12 months; less competitive keywords rank faster. Publishing 30 articles monthly compresses the timeline significantly.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I do contractor SEO myself?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, with adequate time investment. Budget 10–15 weekly hours for research, writing, GBP management, citations, and reviews. Most contractors lack this availability between job sites and client calls. Tools like theStacc handle content automatically for $99/month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Are expensive SEO tools worth it for contractors?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Value depends on output versus cost, not price alone. A $299/month review tool only pays off if you're completing 20+ jobs monthly. A $99/month content tool pays off for almost any contractor since content compounds indefinitely.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the difference between local SEO and regular SEO for contractors?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Local SEO emphasizes Maps visibility, GBP optimization, citations, and "near me" searches. Organic SEO focuses on website content, keywords, backlinks, and standard search rankings. Contractors need both: GBP gets you into the local 3-pack; blog content gets you ranking for informational searches like "how much does a kitchen remodel cost."</div>
        </div>
      </div>
